==English==
===Etymology===
From [[piano]] and [[forte]], the Italian and musical term for soft and loud respectively.  An instrument that can be played both quietly and loudly.

===Noun===
'''pianoforte''' (''Plural:'' '''pianofortes''')

#The musical instrument normally referred to as a [[piano]].

